== Brief Biography
Shuyang Li is a Ph.D. candidate at the College of Computer Science and Technology, Nanjing University of Aeronautics and Astronautics (NUAA).
He is supervised by [https://person.zju.edu.cn/0025078 Prof. Qiang Wu], National-level High-level Talents, doctoral advisor, and Qiushi Distinguished Professor at Zhejiang University.
His co-supervisor is [https://faculty.nuaa.edu.cn/wangran/zh_CN/index.htm Prof. Ran Wang], a doctoral advisor and professor at NUAA.


To date, he has published 13 papers in CCF-recommended journals and conferences as first author, co-first author, or co-author.
Among these, 7 are first-author papers, 4 are in the CCF-A\/B recommended list, and 7 are in the Q1 \/ Q2 of journals according to the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) Journal Ranking (中科院一区\/二区).
He attended and delivered an oral presentation at IEEE WCNC 2025 in Milan, Italy, one of the three flagship international conferences in communications alongside IEEE ICC and IEEE GLOBECOM.
He participated in the 51st International Exhibition of Inventions Geneva (2026) and won the silver medal.
He also serves as a reviewer for several leading journals in computer networking, including IEEE/ACM ToN, IEEE TMC, IEEE TCOM and IEEE TWC.


